            <p>Dance is a performing art form consisting of sequences of movement, either improvised or purposefully selected. This movement has aesthetic and often symbolic value. Dance can be categorized and described by its choreography, by its repertoire of movements, or by its historical period or place of origin.Dance In Color’s mission is to create lasting systemic change in the performing arts. Not only by bolstering young Black dance students, but also by making sure young artists who are striving for professional dance careers receive the support they need to make sure their aspirations become their realities. At Dance In Color, we want to ensure that students are exposed to dance teachers and choreographers from a variety of racial and ethnic backgrounds. We want to hold performing art studios accountable. Ones day, we dream to expand the change we want to see beyond dance and to other forms of performing arts to create lasting change throughout the entire industry.</p>
